- PRD claim is accurate: `.planning/epics/spk02-z-order-commands/spk02-z-order-commands-brief.md:16`.

2. `/state` from C++ omits both `z` and `focused`; Python API hardcodes them.
- C++ `/state` window JSON is built in `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3099`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3103`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3106` and only emits `id/type/x/y/w/h/title/path` (no `z`, no `focused`).
- Python controller hardcodes fake values in `tools/api_server/controller.py:203` and `tools/api_server/controller.py:204`.
- PRD claim is accurate from API consumer POV: `.planning/epics/spk02-z-order-commands/spk02-z-order-commands-brief.md:17`.

3. Workspace save/restore is order-sensitive already, but only implicitly and with gaps.
- Save traverses desktop child list in z-order and records `focusedIndex`: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3833`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3918`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3954`.
- Restore replays window objects in JSON array order and then re-selects `focusedIndex`: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3524`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3744`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3746`.
- Several restore branches skip `created.push_back(...)`, so `focusedIndex` tracking is incomplete for those types:
  - `room_chat`: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3565`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3572`
  - `scramble`: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3573`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3591`
