  - `text_view`: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3609`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:3617`

4. Other hidden z-order assumptions exist outside the spike PRD.
- Terminal fallback picks “frontmost/first found by traversal” terminal: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5023`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5043`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5058`.
- Browser fetch picks the last browser encountered in traversal (“most recently inserted” assumption): `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5065`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5071`, `app/wwdos_app.cpp:5073`.
- Existing explicit z manipulation already exists (good precedent):
  - Send-to-back menu: `app/wwdos_app.cpp:1156`
